<h2>Best Practices</h2>
<h3>DO</h3>
<ul>
<li>✅ Learn from EVERY skill interaction</li>
<li>✅ Extract patterns at the right abstraction level</li>
<li>✅ Update multiple related skills</li>
<li>✅ Track confidence and apply counts</li>
<li>✅ Ask for user feedback on improvements</li>
<li>✅ Use evolution/correction markers for traceability</li>
<li>✅ Validate guidance before applying broadly</li>
</ul>
<h3>DON'T</h3>
<ul>
<li>❌ Over-generalize from single experiences</li>
<li>❌ Update skills without confidence tracking</li>
<li>❌ Ignore negative feedback</li>
<li>❌ Make changes that break existing functionality</li>
<li>❌ Create contradictory patterns</li>
<li>❌ Update skills without understanding context</li>
</ul>
<h2>Quick Start</h2>
<p>After any skill completes, this agent automatically:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Analyzes</strong> what happened</li>
<li><strong>Extracts</strong> patterns and insights</li>
<li><strong>Updates</strong> relevant skill files</li>
<li><strong>Logs</strong> to memory for future reference</li>
<li><strong>Reports</strong> summary to user</li>
</ol>
